<% content_for :title do %>Openproject Configuration<% end %>
<h1><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-check"></i>OpenProject Configuration Guide</h1>
<p>
<%= link_to image_tag("projmgt4.png",:size => '250x120', alt: "Project Mgt"  ), page_path('projmgt'),class: 'pull-left' %>        	

		<p> The following documents an approach to configuring OpenProject for basic use in small and medium business. 
			It shows how to get the base install ready for use as a projet management server and also as a daily operational management server
			if you want to expand its operation. </p> 
			
		<p> I will assume that we are going to run to small projects that are related. We will define a simple waterfall set of 
			plans for each and we will track hours as a well as tasks during the run phases of the projects and store the main project documents.
			The project will run in the context of IT operations and is not viewed as a standalone piece of work. 
			Below shows this simple approach to project management.
			</p>
        							 		
		<hr /><%= link_to image_tag("openproject/opprocess1.png",:size => '450x500', alt: "Project Mgt"  ), class: 'centre' %> 
		

<h2>Configuration </h2>

<h3> Configuring the Plugins </h3>

			<ul>
				<li>Using a web browser, open the project server on your local host or go the servers IP address if you are using Amazon or some other service provider</li> 
				<li>Login as admin pwd admin</li>
				<li>Open the Administration Module</li> 
				<li>Go to the plugin page at the bottom of the menu.</li>							
			</ul>




<h5>Configure the Help link	</h5>
<p> Accept the default. We will not be using this module.</p>
<h5>Configure the Costs Plugin</h5>
<p>Accept the default. We will not be using this module.</p>
<h5>Configure the backlog Plugin</h5>
<p>You access the configuration screen as below</p>
<%= link_to image_tag("openproject/plugin1.png",:size => '450x500', alt: "Project Mgt"  ), class: 'centre' %> 

<p>Use the shift button to select the group of project types that can be used in the initial story process. 
	Use none, bug, feature and support and “phase” as the task type. Do not enter a sprint wiki template name.</p>
	
<%= link_to image_tag("openproject/backlog1.png",:size => '450x500', alt: "Project Mgt"  ), class: 'centre' %>


<p>Press “apply” to save the choice you have made.</p>

<h5>Updating Roles and Permissions</h5>

<p>Add all the roles used in your department that are important. The roles should cover the spectrum of IT services
	and project management as well as key business roles.
	</p>
	<p>A suggested set of roles to choose from</p>
			<ul>
				<li>IT Roles</li>
				<ul>
					<li>IT Manager</li>
					<li>Project Manager</li>
					<li>PMO</li>
					<li>System Administrator</li>
					<li>DBA</li>
					<li>Network</li>
					<li>Help Desk</li>
					<li>Application Administrator</li>
					<li>Tester</li>
					<li>Developer</li>
